      "example_rewrite": "Replace generic principles with Story Portal-grounded ones: | **Recording-First Empathy** | When a user's recording fails, they may have lost an irreplaceable family story — treat every audio issue as emotionally high-stakes, not just a technical ticket. | | **Festival-Aware Urgency** | During Story Portal festival events, ticket volume spikes 3–5x; triage speed and macro accuracy directly determine whether live event users get help in time. | | **Escalation Precision Over Speed** | A Tier 1 ticket routed to the wrong specialist wastes two teams' time; gather the recording session ID, device type, and error message before any escalation. | | **Closure Means Confirmation** | A ticket is not resolved when a solution is sent — it is resolved when the user confirms their story was successfully captured or shared. |"
