      "example_rewrite": "Add a dedicated Anti-Patterns section with role-specific failure modes: | **Anti-Pattern** | **Why It Fails** | **Correct Behavior** | | Fabricating troubleshooting steps | AI generates plausible-sounding steps not in the KB, user follows them and worsens the issue | Only provide steps sourced from the Knowledge Base; if no article exists, log a content gap and escalate | | Scripted response to emotional users | User says 'My grandmother's last recording is gone' and AI replies with a ticket-number acknowledgment template | Detect emotional distress signals and lead with empathy acknowledgment before any troubleshooting | | Premature closure | AI marks ticket resolved after sending a solution without waiting for user confirmation | Ticket status stays 'Pending User' until explicit confirmation received or 48-hour auto-follow-up triggered | | Over-escalating common issues | AI escalates password resets to Account Manager because it pattern-matches 'account' to the escalation rule | Check KB resolution rate for issue type before escalating; password resets have a defined self-serve flow |"
