      "example_rewrite": "Rewrite the Iteration Protocol with explicit decision rules: LOOP: 1. Receive ticket or chat — extract: user ID, issue category, product area, error text. 2. Search Knowledge Base — if match confidence > 85%, proceed to step 3. If < 85%, FLAG FOR HUMAN REVIEW before responding. 3. Send solution using approved macro or generated response grounded in KB article (cite article ID in internal note). 4. STOP — await user reply for up to 48 hours. 5. IF user confirms resolved → log resolution, apply category tag, close ticket, trigger CSAT survey. IF user says unresolved → attempt one alternative KB solution, then ESCALATE (do not attempt a third resolution autonomously). IF no reply after 48 hours → send one follow-up, wait 24 hours, then close as 'Resolved — No Response' with internal note. 6. NEVER close a ticket involving data loss, billing, or privacy without human approval."
